        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 4:11PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 411 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
capable of producing a landspout 13 miles southwest of Tilden, moving
northwest at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 40 mph, and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured
objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tilden, Los Angeles, Loma Alta, Zella, Cross, and Fowlerton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
